{
  "stem": "1338.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He never really had a knack for it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think that-- at heart, I think he was a socialist.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he lost everything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we became really very, very poor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "By the '35, we lost the apartment.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We were thrown out of the house that he built, or the apartment that he built, because he couldn't pay taxes.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I went to the most expensive school in the country.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It's a Hebrew high school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And my father, of course, when I started could afford it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "By the tail end of before World War II, he could hardly afford it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I know, not convinced, I know that he was hungry.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he still insisted on doing that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I remember discussions in the family-- and usually the sisters.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "You know, there's a clan.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The sisters were always together and always discussing everybody, you know, like in any other society, I guess.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And so the sisters, I remember one of them-- which I probably never forgave her-- said that, that's OK.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He can go to public school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It doesn't matter if he doesn't finish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "High school was not obligatory.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "In those days, very few people went to high school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "You just got seven, eight years of primary education and you were out in the labor market.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Hebrew--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Hebrew high school was formed in such a way that even though we had the required division of six years primary school, say, and four years junior and two years-- and then two years, they call it lyceum, final two years.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had the same division as required by the rules of the country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the school was always the same.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
